We have recommended Management to:

a.)	utilize fully idle or dormant trust funds pursuant to the law governing said grant and/or the Memorandum of Agreement/contract with the respective donors;

b.)	implement proper liquidation of the amount granted as well as the refund of excess project funds to the donor, if so provided in the terms of the grant.

3.8 We have recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
a.) Create an Inventory Committee to conduct a complete physical count of the existing local road network to facilitate the preparation of the RPCLRN;
b.) Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road network;
c.) Require the GSO to maintain a Local Road Inventory; Road Map; and Local Road Network Property Card; and
d.) Require the Municipal Accountant to disclose in the Notes to FS the total road network of the Municipality.

We recommended Management to:
a. impose the immediate liquidation of all outstanding advances;
b. avoid granting additional cash advance until the previous cash advances have been liquidated;
c. in cases of excessive cash advance, require the Accountable officer to return or refund excess cash immediately any excess thereof; and by returning it to the Municipal Treasurer’s Office.
d. monitor the timely liquidation of cash advances by sending reminders to accountable officers.

We recommended and Management agreed to:
a. require the Municipal Accountant to implement strictly the guidelines provided under LBC No. 103 dated May 15, 2013, on the grant of Representation and Transportation Allowances to all LGU officials entitled thereto;
b. cause the refund of overpaid RATA as identified herein;
c. through the Vice-Mayor, as the presiding chair of the SB, instigate the adoption/inclusion of rules in the IRP on the work schedules/performance standards of all members, which shall be used in the determination of percentage of RATA to be granted hereafter, in accordance with Item 7.5 of the above LBC; and
d. observe the rules on leave of absence.

We recommended Management to:
a. advise the Municipal Engineer to exert more effort to fast track implementation of all approved and legislated PPAs within the time frame to allow early utilization by the beneficiaries of these PPAs;
b. consider hiring additional personnel to assist in facilitating the implementation of unimplemented projects programmed under the Development Fund, DRRMF, and Share in National Wealth with the objective of eliminating all backlogs in project implementation by end of CY 2017;
c. instruct the Local Finance Committee to monitor and assess the implementation of projects and inform the Municipal Mayor on the result thereof; and
d. review status of unimplemented programs/projects funded in prior years and if found no longer feasible recommend to the Municipal Development Council for reversion, re-appropriation or re-programming to more relevant PPAs for better delivery of services to the constituents.
